This is the unaired episode from Thursday. Hence the weird release date. (The Saturday episode is always a rerun.)

Bernie Sanders is raking in the donors. He's really hitting Hillary hard and Kennedy couldn't be happier.

Bernie Sanders is gaining traction against Clinton. What's sustaining this socialist groundswell? DAVE SMITH, JIMMY FAILLA, and KAYLEIGH McENANY discuss. Joe Biden has said he isn't going to include himself in the first debates. Hillary is still worried. She's started incorporating Joe snubs into her rhetoric. Only one Republican is slated for being in lower tier of the next Republican debates. Sadly it's Rand Paul. Will he debate himself?

OLD SCHOOL vs NEW SCHOOL: DR. MARY ELLEN WEBER, nasa astronaut vs PETER SUDERMAN, reason magazine. Should space travel be public or private? 

The panel returns to talk about an app that is basically Yelp for people. Stephen Hawking is afraid of an alien invasion. Hospitals in the united states are being required to adopt internationally developed standards called ICD10. They are codes that detail someones manner of death or injury. There are 70,000+ different codes detailing different things.

SAMANTHA BROWN and CHRIS GRUNDY of 50/50 are here. They host a show where random people are approached on the street and offered 50 hours of adventure worth 50,000 dollars. The catch? You've got the leave right away.

Nightcap. Mailbag.
